{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_rigoletto_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608786/1958060901/0835.xml":{"full_text":"G. 0. P. Sees Recovery\nShifting Political Tide\nBy the Associated Press\nRepublicans are banking heavily on economic recovery to\nreverse the political tide that now appears to be running\n\u2022gainst them.'\nDemocrats generally believe the business slunjp already\nhas lasted too long for an autumn upturn to affect the political\naituation materially.\nSenator Knowland. Republican of California, said that\nwhile he doesn\u2019t regard it as,\nthe only fgetor, he thinks the i\neconomic downturn had a great i\ndeal to do with his showing in\nlast week\u2019s California pri-\nmaries.\nAlthough he won the Re\npublican nomination for Gov\nernor of California. Senator\nKnowland trailed Democratic\nAttorney General Edmund G.\n(Pat) Brown by 600,000 votes\nIn the total cast for both par-\nties. Both candidates ran on\nboth tickets, and will oppose\neach other in November.\n\u201cI think the recession has hit\nbottom in California and that\nthe economy is on the way up,\u201d 1\nSenator Knowland said in an\ninterview, \u201cbut the average j\nvoter, who might know per-\naonally two or three people who\nwere out of work, probably\nwasn\u2019t aware of any upturn\nwhen he voted in the primary.\u201d\nHowever, Senator Mansfield.\nAssistant Senate Democratic\nLeader who was renominated\nin Tuesday's Montana primary,\nPaul Mellon\nGives Yale\nsls Million\nNEW HAVEN. Conn., June 9\n(IP). \u2014Yale University has re\nceived sls million to build two\nnew residential colleges and ex\npand its educational program.\nThe gift is from the Old Do\nminion Foundation, estbalished\nby Financier Paul Mellon.\nDh A. Whitney Griswold,\npresident of Yale, announced\nthe gift at Class day exercises\nyesterday.\nThe two new colleges, to be!\nbuilt on sites acquired from the\neity of New Haven, will bring\nYale\u2019s total of residential col\nleges to 12. Each residential\ncollege has 300 members di\nvided equally among sopho\nmores, juniors and seniors,\ni Residential freshmen live in\ndormitories.\nL The expanded educational\nprogram will include seminars\nfor all sophomores.\nDr. Griswold said the grant\nrill permit a \u201cmodest increase\u201d\nn the number of undergrad\nThe Mighty Chrysler\nMAKES DRMNff^CIfING\nI I flp CjS II The excitement of knowing you\u2019re\nV mmMM Mm saving money every mile you\ndrive...the excitement of easier,\nV'A, ewA to Pl\n'A Take to the road and see for yourself how different\nat 0L V driving can be when you\u2019re at the wheel of a\nt big, brawny, beautiful Chrysler.\ng- M/Pk jP*\" Turn ahead? Touch the wheel and you\u2019re around!\nv Rough road below? You\u2019d never suspect it. Mister,\n1 _ this car is a Chrysler!\nT. jl jjt ALs y* Every bit as exciting as Chrysler\u2019s feel behind the\nwheel is the fact that it costs you less to drive.\nV/ Chrysler averaged more miles per gallon than any\n_ other car in this year\u2019s Mobilgas Economy Run!\nk The same engineering skill that makes Chrysler\nV jLg, economy champion also brings you such basic auto-\nM JR\u2014 motive advancements as Auto-Pilot. This amazing\nTicfcr -k new invention warns you when you go too fast, lets\nV- you cruise with your foot off the gas pedal, releases\n4 automatically at a touch of the brake.\nBut here\u2019s the most exciting news of all! It\u2019s sur-\nDm, prisingly easy to own a Mighty Chrysler. Find out\nnow at your Chrysierdeajer'i.\n_ y' m/Ti- W.\\ Ft\u201d\nMr ,4nL\n\nMIGHTY CHRYSLER styled to excite engineered to endure priced to please. See it at\nYOUR CHRYSLER DEALER\nsaid he regards the results in\nCalifornia as very encouraging\nfor Democratic hopes of\nstrengthening party control of\nboth houses. He attributed the\nheavy Democratic vote in part\nto economic conditions.\n\u201cOs course a lot of things can!\nhappen between now and\nNovember but the indications\nare that we are going to pick\nup some more seats,\u201d Mansfield\nsaid.\nMost politicians think the'\naverage voter is inclined to\nblame the party In control of\nthe White House for hard times.\nAsked if he believes there will\nbe sufficient business recovery\nto overcome that tendency,\nSenator Mansfield replied:\n\"I hope there will be a quick\neconomy recovery, regardless of\nhow that may affect the politi\ncal situation. But I believe\nthe recession has gone on too\nlong for any fall upturn to as-\nIfect it much.\u201d\nuates that can be admitted to\nYale.\nMr. Mellon, a Yale graduate\nin 1929, lives in Upperville, Va.\nHis late father, Andrew Mellon,\nwas Secretary of the Treasury.\nJapanese Prince\nArrives in U. S.\nSAN FRANCISCO, June 9\n(iP). \u2014Emperor Hirohito\u2019s bro\nther, Prince Tahakito Mikasa,\nand his wife arrived by Japan\nAir Lines plane yesterday en\nroute to South America.\nConsul General Akira Nishi\nyama and his wife headed a\ngroup which met the royal visi\nitors at International Airport.\nThe prince and princess flew\nto San Francisco from Hono\nlulu. where they were guests\nSaturday night of the consul\ngeneral, Hisaji Hattori. They\nare due in Brazil Wednesday\nfor a festival celebrating the\n50th anniversary of Japanese\nimmigration there.\nThe 42-year-old prince,\nyoungest brother of Japan s\nemperor, and his princess will\nleave Tor South America late\ntonight.\nNo press conference was\nscheduled while they are here.\nSlates' Rights\nFight Impends\nIn Congress\nBy t.h\u00ab AaweUUd Pre\u00bb\u00ab\nThe House appeared today to\nbe in for a States\u2019 rights fight,\npossibly this month, with the\nissues ranging into raciil mat\nters and the proper role of the\nSupreme Court.\nThe ro wis over a 10-line bill\napproved by a sharply divided\nHouse Judiciary Committee.\nRival reports were being put in\nfinal form today by proponents,\nled by Southern Democrats, but\nincluding some Republicans,\nand opponents led by the com\nmittee chairman. Republican\njCeller, Democrat of New York.\nThe bill would declare that\nno law passed by Congress shall\nbe considered to supersede or\nexclude State laws on the same\nsubject unless Congress ex\npressly so provides, or unless\nthe Federal and State laws are\nin such \u201cdirect and positivi\nFALL\nPerfect tinfe to see Europe! It\u2019s less crowded In\nAutumn choice accommodations aboard and\nashore! Thrift Season rates start Sept. 1... more\nfor your money wherever you go.\nFUN\nAll kinds of thrilling experiences to enjoy! Tha\nBrussels Fair, Lourdes Centennial. plus the\nextra vacation of your fun-filled Cunard crossing.\nCUNARD\nYour choice of 43 Thrift Season crossings between\nSept. 1-Nov. 30 by 11 Cunard liners at rates as\nlow' as $174! Regular weekly sailings by the\nworld\u2019s largest superliners Queen Elizabeth and\nQueen Mary. Summer season accommodations still\navailable, too. First Class from July 9, Cabin Class\nfrom July 26, Tourist Class from August 16.\nSee your travel agent toon\n&9 C U N A It'D\n7Zua\u00a3 <4 rfa 7u*ef\nCunard Line, 914 15ui Street N.W.\nI conflict\u201d that they cannot be:\n[reconciled.\nI Proponents say such a con\ngressional declaration is need\ned to save vital State laws\nwhich Congress never intended\nto invalidate.\nOffered (y Smith\nThe bill was introduced by\nRepresentative Smith, Demo\ncrat of Virginia, author of the\nFederal Antisubversive Act It\n;was specifically inspired by a\nSupreme Court decision re\nversing the conviction of Com\nmunist Leader Steve Nelson\nunder a Pensylvania sedition\nact. The high court held the\nthis field.\nOpponents of the measure\ncontend it would be unconsti\ntutional. since it would amount\nto amending by simple statute\nthe constitutional article estab\nlishing the supremacy of Fed\nthat in practice it would create\nFederal statute pre-empted\neral law. They also contend\nwidespread confusion over the\nvalidity of old State laws in\nmany fields, such as transpor\ntation and labor-management\nrelations, where the standards\nset b